{"ID":270273, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"273\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs272.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs274.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 273<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">Ghost.<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> Zacharias was a priest of God, and officiating in the Temple,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> and John was a priest after his\n  father, and held the keys of the Aaronic Priesthood,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> and was called of God to preach the Gospel of\n  the kingdom of God.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> The Jews, as a nation, having departed from the law of God<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> and the Gospel\n  of the Lord,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> prepared the way for transferring it to the Gentiles.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">But, says one, the kingdom of God could not be set up in the days of John, for John said the\n  kingdom was at hand.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> But I would ask if it could be any nearer to them than to be in the hands of\n  John. The people need not wait for the days of Pentecost<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> to find the kingdom of God, for John had\n  it with him, and he came forth from the wilderness crying out, &ldquo;Repent ye, for the kingdom of\n  heaven is nigh at hand,&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> as much as to say, &ldquo;Out here I have got the kingdom of God, and you can\n  get it, and I am coming after you; and if you don&rsquo;t receive it, you will be damned;&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> and the\n  scriptures represent that all Jerusalem went out into John&rsquo;s baptism.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> There was a legal\n  administrator, and those that were baptized were subjects for a king;<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> and also the laws and oracles\n  of God were there; therefore the kingdom of God was there; for no man could have better authority\n  to administer than John; and our Savior submitted to that authority Himself, by being baptized by\n  John;<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> therefore the kingdom of God was set up on the earth, even in the days of John.<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Kingdom and Its Fruits<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">There is a difference between the kingdom of God and the fruits and blessings that flow from\n  the kingdom;<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> because there were more miracles, gifts, visions, healings, tongues, &amp;c., in the days\n  of Jesus Christ and His apostles, and on the day of Pentecost, than under John&rsquo;s administration, it\n  does not prove by any means that John had not the kingdom of God, any more than it would that a\n  woman had not a milkpan because she had not a pan of milk, for while the pan might be compared\n  to the kingdom, the milk might be compared to the blessings of the kingdom.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">John was a priest after the order of Aaron,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and had the keys of that priesthood,<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> and came\n  forth preaching repentance and baptism for the remission of sins,<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> but at the same time cries out,\n  &ldquo;There cometh one mightier than I after me, the latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to stoop\n  down and<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108403\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108403)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108403)\">Luke 1:15<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114668\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114668)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114668)\">D&amp;C 84:27<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108401\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108401)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108401)\">Luke 1:8-9<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113229\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113229)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113229)\">D&amp;C 13:1<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114678\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114678)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114678)\">D&amp;C 84:28<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108309\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108309)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108309)\">Mark 1:14<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107576\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107576)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107576)\">Dan. 9:11<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107720\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107720)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107720)\">Mal. 2:8<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110982\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110982)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110982)\">1 Ne. 13:24<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108143\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108143)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108143)\">Matt. 21:33-45<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107765\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107765)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107765)\">Matt. 3:2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">9. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108914\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108914)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108914)\">Acts 2:1-4<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">10. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107766\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107766)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107766)\">Matt. 3:2<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111867\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111867)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111867)\">Alma 9:25<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">11. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107775\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107775)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107775)\">Matt. 3:7-12<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">12. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107771\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107771)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107771)\">Matt. 3:5-6<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">13. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108692\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108692)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108692)\">John 6:15<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">14. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107788\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107788)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107788)\">Matt. 3:13-17<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">15. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107944\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107944)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107944)\">Matt. 11:12<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">16. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108145\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108145)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108145)\">Matt. 21:43<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112079\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112079)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112079)\">Alma 29:17<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114714\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114714)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114714)\">D&amp;C 84:58<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115249\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115249)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115249)\">D&amp;C 101:100<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">17. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110210\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110210)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110210)\">Heb. 7:11<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">18. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113230\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113230)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113230)\">D&amp;C 13:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">19. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108444\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108444)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108444)\">Luke 3:3<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n<\/div>"}